    <title>What&#39;s the difference between an image, photo, and a picture 的区别</title>
    <link href="http://ted423.github.io/Document/Picture/"/>
    <id>http://ted423.github.io/Document/Picture/</id>
    <published>2022-05-19T11:16:50.257Z</published>
    <updated>2022-05-19T11:23:26.196Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>来源: <a href="https://www.computerhope.com/issues/ch000169.htm">https://www.computerhope.com/issues/ch000169.htm</a></p><p>Digital images, photographs, and pictures<br>Image - Any visual object that’s modified or altered by a computer or an imaginary object created using a computer.<br>Photo or photograph - Anything taken by a camera, digital camera, or photocopier.<br>Picture - A drawing, painting, or artwork created on a computer. A picture is also used to describe anything created using a camera or scanner.</p><p>Digital images, photographs, and pictures<br>Image - 由计算机修改或创建的视觉对象或虚构对象。<br>Photo or photograph - 由照相机、数码相机或复印机拍摄的图像西。<br>Picture - 在计算机上创建的绘图、绘画或艺术品。 Picture还用于描述使用相机或扫描仪创建的图像。理论上Picture包含Image以及Photo</p>]]></content>
    
    
      
      
